  "prompt": "What hotel in Dharamshala Hill-station would be safe for unmarried couples, without the harassment of police, hotel staff, and moral police?",
  "response": "While I can't provide real-time updates or specific hotel recommendations, I can suggest some steps for finding a safe hotel in Dharamshala for unmarried couples:\n\n1. **Check Online Reviews**: Look for hotels that have positive reviews from other unmarried couples. Platforms like TripAdvisor, Google Maps, and Booking.com often have reviews that can provide insights into the experiences of other travelers.\n\n2. **Couples-Friendly Hotels**: Some websites specialize in listing hotels that are friendly to unmarried couples. You can search for \"couples-friendly hotels in Dharamshala\" to find suitable options.\n\n3. **Reputable Chains**: Consider well-known hotel chains, as they are usually more professional and less likely to engage in problematic behavior. They often have policies regarding guest privacy.\n\n4. **Contact Hotels Directly**: Before booking, you can call or email the hotel directly to inquire about their policies regarding unmarried couples. This way, you can gauge their response and determine if you feel comfortable proceeding with the booking.\n\n5. **Location Matters**: Staying in more tourist-oriented areas may also help reduce the likelihood of harassment. Areas popular with travelers are generally more accustomed to diverse couples.\n\n6. **Stay Informed**: Look for local forums or social media groups where travelers share their experiences. This can provide current and relevant information about the environment in Dharamshala.\n\n7. **Check In with a Locals**: If you have contacts in the area or know locals, ask them for recommendations on where to stay.\n\nAlways prioritize your safety and comfort when traveling.",
